<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - DETROIT DIESEL SERIES 60 ENGINE - TROUBLESHOOTING -
        VEHICLE SPEED SENSOR (VSS) - Detroit Diesel
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>VEHICLE SPEED SENSOR (VSS) - Detroit Diesel</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Inspect circuits and connectors as outlined in
                <hotlnk document="s08270_166.xml" xrefid="x0827801">Before Troubleshooting</hotlnk>. When monitoring
                engine functions using an EST, if the vehicle is moving, the EST will display vehicle speed if the
                system is working properly.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="x0827806">
            <title>Inspecting And Adjusting the Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS) - Detroit Diesel</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect engine harness connector (225) from the sensor. Loosen the locknut and remove
                    the sensor. The harness connector and sensor should be free of damage or corrosion. Remove any metal
                    shavings or debris from the sensor.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install the sensor, turn in until the sensor contacts the transmission speedometer
                    gear, then back out
                    <emph type="bold">one full turn.</emph>
                    Tighten locknut to 15 ft-lbs. (20.3 N&#8226;m). This assures that the sensor is adjusted properly
                    for the next test.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS) - Detroit Diesel</title>
            <para>To perform this test construct two test leads using terminals (1680205C1) and suitable length of 16GA
                wire.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>A jack must never be used alone to support vehicle. The jack may lower and serious injury
                        could result. Always support vehicle with floor jacks. Always block wheels to prevent vehicle
                        from moving.
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <warning>
                    <para>EXTREME CAUTION should be used to prevent personal injury resulting from contact with rotating
                        vehicle wheels when connecting test leads.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0827810" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS)</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.73in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="1.00in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.72in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.76in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.40in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With VSS (225) disconnected, use test lead to measure resistance to ground at both
                                    sensor terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>VSS (225), term. to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace VSS. (Refer to Inspecting and Adjusting the Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS) -
                                    Detroit Diesel, above).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Use test leads and measure resistance between VSS (225) sensor terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Across term. of VSS (225).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>600 to 900 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace VSS (refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0827806">Inspecting and Adjusting the Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS) -
                                        Detroit Diesel</hotlnk>).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Block front wheels and place rear axles on floor stands.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">CAUTION: Use AC voltmeter with sufficient length leads to avoid
                                        personal contact with rotating vehicle wheels during this test.</emph>Connect
                                    meter leads to test leads.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Run engine at idle speed, with transmission in high gear. Measure voltage across
                                    the two VSS (225) sensor terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Across term. of VSS (225).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>>2.0 volts AC.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>VSS checks good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace VSS (refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0827806">Inspecting and Adjusting the Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS) -
                                        Detroit Diesel</hotlnk>).
                                    <emph type="bold">NOTE: Improper adjustment will cause low, erratic, or no sensor
                                        output.
                                    </emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS) Circuits To ECM - Detroit Diesel</title>
            <table id="t0827811" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS) Circuits To ECM - Detroit Diesel</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.88in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.41in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With VSS sensor (225) disconnected, remove ECM connector (341). At connector (341)
                                    measure resistance to ground at terminal E2, (circuit 97AJ).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(341), E2 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short to ground, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (341) measure resistance to ground at terminal E3 (circuit 97AK).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(341), E3 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short to ground, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (341) measure resistance between terminals E2 and E3 (circuits 97AJ
                                    and 97AK).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(341), E2 to E3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short between circuits 97AJ and 97AK, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (341) measure voltage from E2 (circuit 97AJ) to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(341), E2 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60;1 volt.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short in circuit 97AJ to unwanted voltage source, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (341) measure voltage from E3 (circuit 97AK) to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(341), E3 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60;1 volt.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short in circuit 97AK to unwanted voltage source, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (225), use test leads to connect circuit 97AJ to ground. At connector
                                    (341) measure resistance from E2 (circuit 97AJ) to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(341), E2 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97AJ between connectors (225) and (341),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (225), use test leads to connect circuit 97AK to ground. At connector
                                    (341) measure resistance from E3 (circuit 97AK) to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(341), E3 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>The VSS circuits between connectors (341) and (225) check good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97AK between connectors (225) and (341),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
